address: 230 W Tree Frog Ln, Shelton, WA 98584
Description: Incredible investment/sweat equity opportunity! Sprawling 1.2 acre gated property at the end of a private county road. Roll up your sleeves, finish junk removal and renovate the interior spaces to your liking. Structure has good bones and life left in the roof. Single story 1,742 SF, 3 bedroom, 1.5 bath, 2 large separate living areas. 2 car attached garage, plus 670 SF shop that fits 1-car and RV/large boat. Pool and hot tub/spa are not functional, but can be repaired. Propane available, tank was removed and line capped. Being sold “AS-IS”. Just outside city limits and minutes to 101!

Pride of workmanship really shines through in this stunning Lake Stevens remodel. House has been completely renovated from floor to ceiling boasting brand new interior and exterior paint, 3cm countertops, new cabinets, brand-new stainless-steel Samsung appliance package, vaulted ceilings, and more! With 4 bedrooms there is plenty of space for a guestroom or even a second office for working from home. Incredibly spacious 3 car garage. Oversized nearly half acre corner lot with peekaboo views of Lake Stevens and the Cascades. Fully fenced backyard also has a fabulous gazebo and huge deck that is perfect for entertaining your guests and a large gravel area with a huge 14’ double drive gate allows you plenty of room to park your RV or boat.

Set up to be the perfect 'small' homestead. The property includes a spacious move-in ready home, 1-acre lot, detached shop/garage with separate electric meter, RV parking, and tons of potential to make the yard your own. Home boasts new carpeting, luxury vinyl plank wood flooring, interior and exterior paint, updated bathrooms with new vanities, and fixtures. The large kitchen has been renovated with all new cabinets, butcherblock countertops, and new stainless steel appliances. Tons of natural light fills the home with new windows and sliding glass door. Plenty of room with endless opportunities with no HOA or CC&Rs.

address: 16684 Agate Pass Rd NE, Bainbridge Island, WA 98110
Description: Welcome to your island sanctuary! This fabulous, light-filled home with open floor plan, recently renovated kitchen, nestled on private, spacious grounds, with mature landscaping, will make heads turn!  Featuring gleaming red oak floors, custom barn-wood beams, barn door, cozy wood burning stove with artistic tile surround, private upstairs main suite, and an open chefs' kitchen at the heart of the home. Granite countertops, stainless appliances and a professional gas range inspire! Your 1 acre parcel, is insulated by a wooded buffer, and the pond will make you want to relax in an Adirondack chair and watch the wildlife or simply soak up the sun. A spacious wrap-around deck pulls it all together. Mere minutes to Bloedel Reserve. This is it!

address: 21910 103rd Street Ct E #21, Bonney Lake, WA 98391
Description: 1979 Fleetwood featuring: 3 bedrooms, and 2 bathrooms totaling 1074 square feet. This home has been remodeled.  Featured upgrades include: a new roof, upgraded countertops, new siding, and renovated bathrooms. Also featured: a large deck, new cabinets throughout the home, new flooring/carpet, and it all sits on a massive lot (partially fenced). All-ages community. Come make it yours!

address: 13735 15th Ave NE APT A17, Seattle, WA 98125
Description: Updated top floor unit with vaulted ceilings. New exterior siding and walkways just completed this fall. Additional renovations are nearing completion.  Kitchen has quartz counters, designer tile back splash & floors, stainless appliances, undermount sink & eating bar. Spacious Living/dining rooms, fireplace & full-size utility room. Primary w/modern bath, garden tub, newer carpets, paint, vanity & quartz counters. Walk in closets. Updated second full bath w/newer flooring & quartz counters. Clubhouse amenities include a pool, sauna, and indoor jacuzzi. Covered parking, generous storage, and adjacent to Jackson Park golf course and trail. Convenient to light rail at Northgate, with additional light rail coming soon at 145th.

address: 2005 Glen Erin Dr, Walla Walla, WA 99362
Description: This ranch style home features 4 bedrooms, 2 full baths, and 2400 square feet. Walking through the door you are greeted with an abundance of natural light and a cozy wood burning fireplace. Spacious living room and open concept kitchen are perfect for entertaining. The sliding glass door walks you out to a lovely back patio and a generous sized backyard with mature landscaping. Vinyl windows and new energy efficient ductless mini splits. The basement has been fully renovated with new flooring, interior paint, and updated bathroom. Laundry room and utility room downstairs. This property is currently rented through 6/30/22. Welcome home!

CASH BUYERS, this affordable manufactured home is on .63 acres close to shopping, schools, freeway on ramps and parks. The home has been completely renovated and is in good condition. The kitchen cabinets, counter tops and back splash, flooring, and appliances are updated. Both bathroom have also been updated with tile floors and surround. All rooms include updates. The home includes 3 bedrooms and a family room. There are a few add-on stick-built structure which increase size. The front of the home includes a large covered deck and patio for entertaining. Garden space and fruit trees are in the large yard. Storage sheds and carport. Lots of parking. CASH ONLY.

Spacious home on more than 5 acres with $200,000 worth of renovation: new roof, siding, window, floors, kitchen, new paint, lighting, & fixtures. Main level features primary BR, additional BR, 2 bathrooms, living room with fireplace, kitchen, & dining room. Extended family living basement features living room with slider to backyard, 3 additional BRs, bathroom, kitchen, & laundry room. Large backyard includes full fencing, barn with 3 stalls & shop/office attached to the barn.

Elegantly renovated and modernized, this stunning 4 BR contemporary is the crown jewel of Clyde Hill. Masterful architecture & design surrounded by open beams, soaring ceilings and walls of windows offering a radiant glow throughout the home. A magnificent chef’s kitchen with a trendy breakfast nook, an impressively grand quartz island and privileged views of Lake WA and Seattle. Relax in the Primary Suite’s lavish spa-like bath with its soothing tranquil view and endless closets. Designer finishes throughout complement 3 spacious open living and entertaining areas. Brand new decks and landscaping surrounds this savvy, smart-wired home with generously sized bedrooms. A desirable & spectacular oasis. The absolute epitome of luxurious living.

Prepare to be enchanted! Sweeping sound & mountain views from every room of this stunning Steilacoom retreat.  Gorgeous Western Exposure, perched on the hillside against a beautiful treetop canopy. Fresh deep green exterior paint & multiple decks and balconies to relax and soak in the views. Renovated interior features brand new carpets throughout and a cheerful kitchen with repainted cabinets, granite countertops and large center island. Floor-to-ceiling living room windows brighten this delightful space.  Lovely master with vaulted ceilings. 2nd junior master with en-suite bath. Upper level office with private balcony and eye-popping vistas. Full bathroom and 2 extra bedrooms downstairs. EZ walk to Historic Old Town Steilacoom. Wow!

Absolute Must see! Equestrian Farm w/ 2 recently renovated houses sitting on 6.6 acres. A 60 x 30 Barn features a tack room wash stall, adjustable stall system,paddock,office and loft. Enter into a beautiful open concept living flooded w/ natural light. Spacious kitchen features stunning quartz countertops, new flooring and new fixtures throughout. Beautifully designed full bath with double vanity and gold hardware. The stunning 1240 sqft updated two-bedroom and 1.75 bath ADU w/ spacious open living concept,kitchen features quartz countertops, new flooring, and new fixtures. Large Primary suite w/fully updated bath. Large 30 x 26 2 car detached garage and shop. Close to the shopping and restaurants. Call now for a private tour!

Two homes on one property with recent upgrades! Larger home was built in 1938, is 876 sq ft and has 2 bedrooms and 1 full bath which recently had a complete renovation. Interior also remodeled with vinyl plank flooring, ductless heat pump, new roof in 2020, new kitchen stove and a front door ramp. Smaller home was built in 2018, is 552 sq ft and has 1 bedroom and 1 bath as well as an attached 384 sq ft garage and front foyer with a counter and plenty of upper and lower cabinet storage.

Renovated 3 bedroom home on a large fenced lot.  The main floor features a primary bedroom with an ensuite and walk-in closet.  Updates throughout including: electrical, remodeled bathrooms, traffic master carpet with plush pad, and fully repainted inside/out.  New foundation beams, extra insulation, and fiber cement siding. Enjoy the cozy wood-burning fireplace, wainscoting, and refinished hardwood floors. Long driveway with carport and RV/boat parking.  Mature landscaping with fruit trees.
This duplex was under renovation when the contractor walked off the property and shut down their license leaving this project partially finsihed. This duplex is sold AS-IS

Single level, renovated home located in the picturesque Huntington Park. This active 55+ community is surrounded by miles of well manicured nature trails, beautifully maintained gardens, clubhouse, pool, jacuzzi & community activities year-round. Located at the end of a quiet road, you are first greeted by the peaceful courtyard & secluded entry. Inside, the well designed & updated kitchen flows effortlessly to the living & dining space. Sliding door off the living room to your private deck and side yard. Down the hall, both bedrooms have ample space & storage. The primary bedroom is equipped with a walk-in closet. Large windows, flooding each space with natural light. Low HOA fees & full-service yard maintenance. Welcome home!

address: 13055 Pacific Hwy SW UNIT D, Lakewood, WA 98499
Description: Spectacular recently renovated condo, Brand new laminated flooring and carpet. Freshly painted interior/exterior. Down stairs feature a spacious open concept kitchen, laundry, family room. Upstairs features 2 bed 1 full bath with a large storage room.  Beautifully fenced private and landscaped backyard sitting area. NO PET RESTRICTIONS!!! Located minutes from I-5,  JBLM, shopping, and many more amenities. Bus line 206 stop is located immediately in front of the complex. Chambers Bay Golf Course is a short drive away, where you can golf, dine & walk trails!

Newly renovated lower South Hill Condo. Top level and South facing unit. All new flooring, doors, and trim. Kitchen with wood stained shaker cabinets. New tiled shower and vanity. Well maintained central courtyard. Lower South Hill/Cliff Cannon neighborhood offers easy access to I-90, bus line, hospitals, and downtown. Only a few blocks to stores and restaurants. Enjoy all off the South Hill's Historical Parks and Bluff Trails. Included with unit is a designated covered parking stall and storage compartment.

This mid-century building offers large units with in-unit laundry and substantial upside through renovations and rent increases. The building is located on a 5,300SF lot zoned LR3 with significant development potential.    This offering presents the rare opportunity to purchase a well maintained classic building with a considerable value-add opportunity in one of the nation’s fastest growing markets.

address: 7000 Cleopatra Pl NW APT 202, Seattle, WA 98117
Description: Quiet, charming 1BR/1BA condo nestled between Greenwood/Phinney and Ballard, minutes away from Downtown, with stainless steel appliances, new fixtures, painting, carpet and retouches. Located near Take 5 Market, Choice Grocery, Barking Dog Alehouse, 65th St bars, shopping, restaurants along 70th, the 28X bus, D line, and Ballard neighborhoods.   This unit boasts a practical, well-lit, spacious floor plan with large bedroom and ample closet space, dining area, wood-burning fireplace and west-facing balcony with roomy deck storage. Available to occupy or rent out! Part of a small, boutique building, renovated extensively in 2021, with new siding, patio, and roof, it also has 1 car parking in a private garage and entrance.   Come and see it !!

Looking for a newly renovated home to call yours? Here it is, Beautifully updated with a new roof, panel box, ductless  heat pump, laundry room, laminate floors, wall heaters, paint inside & out, plus more. Corner lot, comfortably sized for easy maintenance & still have room for flowers, small garden &/or barbeque area. Also has detached garage or make it a shop. Local diner & market within walking distance. A few short miles from Tenino & around the corner to either Centralia or Tumwater amenities. Located  just outside hustle & bustle of city life to give you the peace & quiet you're looking for.

This beautifully renovated home with 2 large shops offers country living and a tranquil lifestyle in the community of Farmington. Featuring a stunning country kitchen with granite countertops and slate tile flooring, 2 bonus rooms and indoor and outdoor stone patio fireplaces. Second full bath under construction on upper level, will be completed by end of February. Perfect for entertaining, the french doors from the kitchen and dinette open onto the expansive deck. Outside you will find cabin style covered outdoor living with a pass through fireplace, pond water feature, hot tub and charming trees and landscaping which includes four varieties of grapes, as well as apple, pear, walnut and hazelnut trees, black raspberry and loganberries. If you are looking for property for a hobby farm, this is perfect with a chicken coop and large established garden area. Centrally located Farmington is a close drive to Pullman and Spokane and only minutes from over 30 miles of recreational trails at McCroskey State Park.

Investor Alert! Three, potentially 4, income producing units on one lot. Endless Opportunity, an investor's dream!! Main house is rambler a with 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom and charming front porch. Upgraded with new flooring and appliances. Back structure is two story home with separate rental units. Downstairs unit is 2 bedroom one bathroom currently at sheetrock stage of renovation. Upstairs is a studio with a full bath that just needs finishing touches. Spacious driveway in front with room for several cars and paved surface alongside for easy access to the back house.Great lot with large, partially fenced yard. Amazing Location! Near Hwy 167 and 405 for an easy commute, schools, shops, SeaTac airport, Seattle and Bellevue.

Situated in the heart of East Hoquiam and directly across the street from the "Y", which boasts Childcare/Preschool fitness gym (Pilates/Yoga/Weights), a lap pool, wave pool, water slide, saunas, jacuzzi, Tae kwon do, volleyball, racketball, basketball and more, sits this recently renovated and lovely store front property for income potential, along with a beautifully furnished attached 1 bedroom / 1 bath apartment. Included, just next door is an additional detached 2 bedroom / 1 bath house with new paint and a new paved driveway(Alley) between Sumner & Simpson Avenue.  All exterior upgrades makes this property very appealing, the income potential makes it a steal.  Potential 2yr Owner Financing with sizeable down payment.

Newly renovated 2020 high class 90yr-old building with industrial inspired design.  Whole house water filtration system and an extremely efficient building with heat/pump furnace in bottom unit & well-lit exterior. Custom downstairs apartment design for owner occupancy, KitchenAid high-quality matching appliances, gas cooktop range & patio off French door and 1 car garage w/storage.  2 units upstairs; 2bdrm/2ba master suite & 2bdrm/1ba apartment. Stable rental history & below price rent on one-unit, current combined upstairs rents is $2500. Put $200K down, live in downstairs unit & renters will cover most/entire house payment. Walking distance to Downtown Kelso. Buy as a rental or owner occupied. Will sell with furnishings.  Seismic upgrade

Awesome level 2+acre site, well, septic, electricity on site,  value is in land,  no value assigned to moble home which has been vacant for several years but could be renovated.  There is also a large propane tank on site.  This is an estate so buyer will have to test well and septic and verify improvements.
This is a great fixer! Seller will leave all materials purchased for renovations. Home sits on 3 lots with beautifully maintained garden and pool.
